<p>Then <i>d</i> is a metric on <i>X</i> and is called the <b>discrete metric</b>.&emsp;■</p>

<p><b>Examples 3.1.4</b>. The function <i>d</i> : ℝ<sup>2</sup> × ℝ<sup>2</sup> → ℝ given by</p>

<math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" display="block">
  <mi>d</mi>
  <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
  <mo fence="false" stretchy="false">&#x27E8;</mo>
